              The leaving (positive) and the entering (negative) flows and net outranking flow values were computed which are shown in Tables 
              9
               and 
              10
              . After calculating the net outranking flow values for alternatives, the ranking of dangerous sections of the KWCT is obtained, as given in Table 
              11
              . Finally, after applying the hybrid PROMETHEE II-entropy model and obtaining the net flow for four high-risk sections of the KWCT, the zone Hz11 was introduced as the most dangerous section. This result means that the zone Hz11, where the amount of water inflow into the tunnel was very high, is considered the most dangerous section of the tunnel. In other words, it can be said that among the four main hazards in the Kerman water conveyance tunnel, including rock abrasivity, fault zones, squeezing zones, and groundwater inflow, the risk of water inflow into the tunnel is more significant than the other hazards.

